        public void computeMECStates(JDDNode restrict)
                      throws PrismException
        Description copied from class: ECComputer
        Compute states of all maximal end components (MECs) in the submodel obtained by restricting this one to the set of states restrict, and store them. They can be retrieved using ECComputer.getMECStates(). You will need to to deref these afterwards. If restrict is null, we look at the whole model, not a submodel.

      • computeMECStates

        public void computeMECStates(JDDNode restrict,
                             JDDNode accept)
                      throws PrismException
        Description copied from class: ECComputer
        Compute states of all accepting maximal end components (MECs) in the submodel obtained by restricting this one to the set of states restrict, and store them, where acceptance is defined as those which intersect with accept. They can be retrieved using ECComputer.getMECStates(). You will need to to deref these afterwards. If restrict is null, we look at the whole model, not a submodel. If accept is null, the acceptance condition is trivially satisfied.
        Specified by:
        computeMECStates in class ECComputer
        Parameters:
        restrict - BDD for the set of states to restrict to
        accept - BDD for the set of accepting states
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • findEndComponents

        private java.util.List<JDDNode> findEndComponents(JDDNode restrict,
                                                  JDDNode accept)
                                           throws PrismException
        Find all accepting maximal end components (MECs) in the submodel obtained by restricting this one to the set of states restrict, where acceptance is defined as those which intersect with accept. If restrict is null, we look at the whole model, not a submodel. If accept is null, the acceptance condition is trivially satisfied.
        Parameters:
        restrict - BDD for the set of states to restrict to
        accept - BDD for the set of accepting states
        Returns:
        a list of (referenced) BDDs representing the MECs
        Throws:
        PrismException
